1.23.20  11:37 pm   Do you interpret dreams?

     The kind one has when they is asleep, to be specific. I don't have any dreams that need interpreting right now, but I want to know for future reference.

Actually I just realized dream interpretations are probably generally more powerful if the interpreter knows the person of the dream being interpreted, probs most effective it is that person themself,

      but I, thinking about it more now, I think sometimes it is good to get a perspective of a dream from someone unfamiliar with the person who dreamt the dream has.

      This is assuming dreams need interpreting in the first place, which I am not even 100% sure on.
